Class TideCalculator

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.fameit.tide.TideCalculator

  • public class TideCalculator
extends java.lang.Object
    Calculates the tide and tidal extremes (high and low tides) from the tidal constituents.

    • Method Detail

      • calculateTide

        public double calculateTide(long timeInMillis,
                            boolean updateNodal)
        Calculate the current tide (height). Optionally updates the nodal corrections.
        Parameters:
        timeInMillis - time for which to calculate the tide in milliseconds since the java epoch (midnight, January 1, 1970 UTC)
        updateNodal - if true the nodal (long term) correction will be updated
        Returns:
        height (in meters)

      • calculateExtremes

        public TideCalculator.Extreme[] calculateExtremes(long timeInMillis,
                                                  long intervalInMillis)
        Calculates all extremes (high and low tides) in the interval timeInMillis...timeInMillis+intervalInMillis. The nodal corrections are only calculated once to speed up calculations.
        Parameters:
        timeInMillis - start time of the interval for which to calculate the extremes in milliseconds since the java epoch (midnight, January 1, 1970 UTC)
        intervalInMillis - length of the interval for which to calculate the extremes
        Returns:
        extremes in the specified interval as TideCalculator.Extreme objects
